ovation lies in treating compositional reasoning not as a sequence of pre-defined operations, but as a *structured prediction task over executable logical forms*, trained end-to-end with weak supervision from answers and reinforced via consistency checks. This differs fundamentally from prior work: unlike TMNs, it does not rely solely on sub-question generation in natural language; unlike NLC, it avoids hardwiring logic into modules, allowing greater adaptability. It also advances beyond standard CoT by producing semantically grounded, verifiable logic trees.

